SIMPLE: turreted
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Turreted
<hw>Tur"ret*ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Furnished with a
turret or turrets; specifically <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, having the whorls
somewhat flattened on the upper side and often ornamented by spines or
tubercles; -- said of certain spiral shells.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Formed like a tower; <as>as, a <ex>turreted</ex>
lamp</as>.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turrethead</ent>⟦br⟧
